\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. N. lutea} (Desr.) DC. in Lam. & DC.,{\i  Fl. Fr.} ed. 3, {\b 3}: 626 (1805). Setose-hispid and glandular-pubescent annual; stems 10-60 cm, erect or ascending, branched. Leaves 2-7 × 0·5-2 cm, obtuse or acute, entire or dentate. Calyx 6-10 mm at anthesis, 10-20 mm in fruit; teeth ½ as long to almost as long as tube. Corolla 7-12 mm; limb 5-15 mm in diameter, pale yellow, divided to c. ½ into ovate-orbicular lobes. Nutlets 3·5-6 mm, oblong-ellipsoid, rugose, ribbed; collar-like basal ring smooth. 2n = 14. {\i Ukraine and S.E. Russia; a frequent casual in parts of C. & S.E. Europe and locally naturalized.} Rs (W, E) [Hu Ju Rm].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. N. obtusifolia} (Willd.) DC., {\i loc. cit.} (1805). Shortly setose-hispid, eglandular annual; stems 5-15 cm, ascending, usually simple. Leaves 3-5 × c. 1 cm, oblong to ovate-oblong, subentire, subobtuse. Calyx c. 5 mm at anthesis, 8-10 mm in fruit; teeth c. ½ as long as tube. Corolla e. 8 mm; limb 3-6 mm in diameter, blue, divided to c. ½ into ovate-orbicular lobes. Nutlets c. 3 mm, oblong-ovoid, erect, smooth, shiny, blackish; collar-like basal ring smooth.{\i  Aegean region and S.E. Bulgaria; naturalized in C. Italy}. Bu Gr [It].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  {\b  N. rosea} (Bieb.) Link,{\i  Enum. Hort. Berol. Alt.}{\b  1}: 167 (1821), from the Caucasus, with purplish or brownish corolla 15-18 mm long and often slightly ribbed nutlets, is a frequent casual in parts of W. & C. Europe.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. N. pulla} (L.) DC. in Lam. & DC., {\i Fl. Fr.} ed. 3, {\b 3}: 626 (1805). Grey-setose and more or less glandular-pubescent annual to perennial; stems 25-50 cm, erect, usually branched above. Leaves 3-12 × 0·7-2 mm, lanceolate to linear-lanceolate, acute, entire. Calyx 6-8 mm at anthesis, 9-12 mm in fruit; teeth c. 1 as long as tube. Corolla (9-)10-14 mm; limb 5-8 mm in diameter, dark reddish- or blackish-purple (rarely yellowish-white), divided to c. ¼ into broadly ovate lobes. Nutlets 2·5-3 × 3·5-5 mm, obliquely ovoid, ribbed; collar-like basal ring ribbed. 2n = 18, 20. {\i E. & E.C. Europe; locally naturalized further west and progressively extending its area westwards.} Au Bu Cz Ge Gr Hu *Ju Po Rm Rs (*N, *B, C, W, K, E) [Fe Ga He].
